h3. Issue Summary
Page PDF export takes a long time to finish if the page contains a JIRA Issue macro with a JQL query that searches for issues on many projects (20+). This does not seem to affect pages with many issues from the same project, instead, it affects queries that have to look for issues on many projects. In some cases, it may take up a few minutes to export just a single page.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create 20+ projects in Jira > add a single issue to each one of these projects;
# Create a page, add a Jira Issue macro in it > Add a JQL query that retrieve all these spaces > Publish the page;
# Export the page to PDF (*...* > Export > PDF);

h3. Expected Results
* PDF export should be quick, as there should be about 10+ to be retrieved;

h3. Actual Results
* PDF export takes a long time, due to the JQL query retrieving many different projects (even though there is just a single issue on each project)

h3. Workaround
* If possible, narrow down the number of retrieved issues, by excluding some projects or breaking down the page into additional child pages, each reporting on just a few projects at a time.

h3. Issue Summary
When we have the Attachments macro added to a page, the Download All button doesn't work for anonymous users.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Set up [Anonymous Access|https://support.atlassian.com/confluence-cloud/docs/set-up-public-access/] to your site and to a space;
# Create a page and add an image there;
# Publish the page;
# Create a new page and add the attachments macro;
# In the macro properties point to the first page you created;
# Publish the page;
# Copy the page's URL and open it on an incognito window;
# Click over the *Download All* button, in the Attachments macro.

h3. Expected Results
All the attachments should be downloaded.

h3. Actual Results
You are redireted to a page not found message.

*Notes*:
* A 404 is thrown after clicking in the download button: {{https://SITENAME.atlassian.net/wiki/download/all_attachments?pageId=CONTENTID}};
* The original page that has the attachments can be accessed, as well as its image.

h3. Workaround
You can click in each of the attachments to download them individually.
